{"key":"post-5200189","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5200189</id>\n<content>Turn them upside down in your glovebox and dump the liquid out.  84 is WAY too hot for half gallon jars.  I've shot an infrared camera at quart jars and the glass itself was 3.5F warmer than the surrounding shelving.  That means the grains were at least 5F warmer, considering glass is an insulator.  A half gallon jar will produce even more heat.  Use room temperature for incubation.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5200221</next>\n<prev>5199386</prev>\n<first>5199315</first>\n<last>5201046</last>\n<when>1137725582</when>\n<utime>01/20/06 04:53 AM</utime>\n</post>"}